cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes buffer-aided distributed space-time coding schemes and relay selection algorithms for cooperative wireless systems, which involves the transmission and processing of information. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with cooperative wireless systems, which are a type of network, and proposes relay selection algorithms and buffer-aided schemes to improve the quality of transmission. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes algorithms for relay selection and buffer-aided schemes to improve the performance of cooperative wireless systems, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper proposes techniques to improve the quality of transmission in cooperative wireless systems, which can involve the transmission of multimedia data. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper involves the development of algorithms for relay selection and buffer-aided schemes, which can be seen as a computational problem.
